<div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77635758"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77635758,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;gusdizerega&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Gus diZerega&quot;}"></div><a name="star1"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star2" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://gusdizerega.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://gusdizerega.newsvine.com/">Gus diZerega</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77635758" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>The authoritarian nihilism that calls itself conservatism today is not conservative in either the American or the European sense. It cares neither for the heritage of the past nor respecting settled traditions.  It worships power, and domination.  It is our version of the political perils from the right that Europe went through after World War One.  Over there some nations survived and some succumbed.</p>
<p>The jury is out over here.</p></div>
