<p>&ldquo;Their political reactions express rather a profound and largely unconscious hatred of our society and its ways -- a hatred which one would hesitate to impute to them if one did not have suggestive clinical evidence ... The pseudo-conservative, Adorno writes, shows 'conventionality and authoritarian submissiveness' in his conscious thinking and 'violence, anarchic impulses, and<br />chaotic destructiveness in the unconscious sphere&hellip;&hellip; The pseudo conservative is a man who, in the name of upholding traditional American values and institutions and defending them against more or less fictitious dangers,  consciously or unconsciously aims at their abolition.'"</p>
<p>-- Richard Hofstadter, 1965</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637385,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;tcinla&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">7 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77637385" title="Link to this comment">#1.1</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 12:37 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77639102"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77639102,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jimes3861561&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Jimes-3861561&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://jimes3861561.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://jimes3861561.newsvine.com/">Jimes-3861561</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77639102" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>The real game changer is Lac-Megantic, Quebec.  The oil train derailment that destroyed the town and killed over 50 people because a 72 car train with a single engineer was parked for the night and not enough of the brakes were set.  It was an American owned train, probably carrying Koch fracked oil, and definitely with the Kochs approach to workers --- have as few of them as possible, no matter what the safety concerns.</p>
<p>Don't look for the Keystone Pipeline to be approved any time soon.</p>
<p>Even Texas and Oklahoma are feeling the effects of the "non-existent" climate change.  Maybe, just maybe, the Kochs will back off a bit, but don't count on it.</p>
