<p>Does he disclose these "better answers" or is just that their answers would be better by default, because they came from conservatives?</p></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77636878,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;brewerpatriot&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">4 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77636878" title="Link to this comment">#8</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 12:21 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77637033"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637033,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;knitterelf&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;knitterelf&quot;}"></div><a name="star7"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star8" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://knitterelf.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://knitterelf.newsvine.com/">knitterelf</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77637033" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>"better answers" = Ideas from Corporations (and the bigger the corp. the better)</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637033,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;knitterelf&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">6 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77637033" title="Link to this comment">#8.1</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 12:25 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77637403"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637403,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jjames7707275&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;J. James-7707275&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://jjames7707275.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://jjames7707275.newsvine.com/">J. James-7707275</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77637403" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>No kidding. At least liberals put the money where their mouth is, policy-wise. Just because a Republican acknowledges climate change exists (want a cookie?), does not seem to change the fact that it's a post-policy party.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637403,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jjames7707275&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77637403" title="Link to this comment">#8.2</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 12:38 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77641007"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77641007,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;johnseekingenlightenment&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;John seeking enlightenment&quot;}"></div><a name="star8"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star9" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://johnseekingenlightenment.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=johnseekingenlightenment5261D6FA-7B26-00F1-2B9B-742E6557DE91.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://johnseekingenlightenment.newsvine.com/">John seeking enlightenment</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77641007" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>The problem is the 'better answers' consistent with free market ideology are to tax carbon emissions at a rate commensurate with the costs associated with mitigating its impacts.  In economics this is called a 'Pigovian Tax'.  Pigovian Taxes are used to introduce and reform market pricing for an activity that is inadvertently subsidized by the public, such as pollution discharges and impacts on public infrastructure caused by traffic congestion, etc.</p>
<p>Such taxes would include taxing fossil fuels <strong>and</strong> farming and land development practices that lead to degradation of topsoil, which is a leading contributor to increased CO2 emissions. </p>
<p>(All that dark, spongy, organic matter in topsoil is converted to carbon dioxide when the soil is washed into a river.  This is why rivers have sand bars, not soil bars, following each spring flood -- the sand is all that is left from the top soil.)</p>
<p>(Soil erosion is a BIG problem -- imagine the amount of carbon in several feet of topsoil spread out over the entire Midwest.)</p>
<p>GOP are fans of giving businesses a free ride.  They are not fans of businesses paying for the impacts of what they do.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77641007,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;johnseekingenlightenment&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">6 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77641007" title="Link to this comment">#8.3</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 2:24 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77654624"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77654624,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;nathan-1680585&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Nathan-1680585&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://nathan-1680585.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://nathan-1680585.newsvine.com/">Nathan-1680585</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77654624" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Conservatives do have some interesting, market based ideas.  Like Cap &amp; Trade.  That was the conservative plan.  Give companies an economic incentive not to pollute and effectively tax those that do and let the market decide what it's worth.  Wonder what ever happened to their support of that idea?</p>
<p>It's kind of like how they had an interesting, market-based idea for health care of creating public exchanges where individuals could buy coverage from a range of competing companies, while using an individual mandate to ensure fair participation and personal responsibility.  I'm sure they still back that concept, right?  Right?  Why are you laughing?</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77654624,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;nathan-1680585&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77654624" title="Link to this comment">#8.4</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 9:07 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77655039"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77655039,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-richcivil&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Rich Civil&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://fb-richcivil.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=nullD5831A0C-EE29-368B-52A1-979FEF368299.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://fb-richcivil.newsvine.com/">Rich Civil</a><span class="facebookVia">via Facebook</span></div></div><div id="commentText_77655039" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>The above article does contain a link the the complete original article where he does write about his idea.  His idea seems to have some similarities to James Hanson's plan. </p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77655039,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-richcivil&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77655039" title="Link to this comment">#8.5</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 9:23 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77637144"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637144,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;tcinla&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;TCinLA&quot;}"></div><a name="star9"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star10" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://tcinla.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://tcinla.newsvine.com/">TCinLA</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77637144" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Here's an example of a "pro-growth" climate change policy that Republicans could have latched onto not that long ago.  It was actually set up in that bastion of commienism, Berserkeley CA:</p>
<p>The biggest deterrent for most homeowners in going solar is the initial expense of getting the equipment, the re-wiring etc., which can run to $30K+.  So the city council there had the idea that for resident homeowners, the city could give a guarantee for a bank loan for that expense, with the loan to run with the mortgage (i.e., when the house was sold, the new owner would assume the unpaid balance), with the requirement that the equipment purchased be "Made in the USA" and that the homeowner remain there for five years (to avoid the yuppie "flippers").</p>
<p>Think about it:  there's no "government money" being spent, the Made in the USA requirement helps build an industry where US companies are leaders in innovation, but have problems with sales (this is an old old old device for stimulating the manufacturing economy that goes back to Hamilton, f'r chrissakes) and has the result of reducing carbon emissions and increasing individual freedom (homeowners controlling their own energy and selling back the excess to utilities so they can increase their non-carbon energy).  How much more "Republican" does an idea have to get?  Do it nationwide, and what do you have?  New industry, lots of hiring there and in independent small businesses who install the equipment, etc., and "energy independence."</p>
<p>Sadly, this idea makes far too much sense for the modern day ignoramuses of the Confederate Corporate Party.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637144,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;tcinla&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">8 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77637144" title="Link to this comment">#9</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 12:29 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77637390"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637390,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;slappymagoo&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;slappy magoo&quot;}"></div><a name="star10"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star11" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://slappymagoo.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://slappymagoo.newsvine.com/">slappy magoo</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77637390" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Only problem is it's un-American to not keep paying an American corporation for your electricity if you're getting it free from the sun. It's only patriotic if it comes from Middle Eastern oil. And if you ask why, you hate America.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637390,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;slappymagoo&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">7 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77637390" title="Link to this comment">#9.1</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 12:37 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77637636"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637636,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;giantkid&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Giant Kid&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://giantkid.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://giantkid.newsvine.com/">Giant Kid</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77637636" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Great way to get more solar on the market, TC.</p>
<p>All we have to do to implement it nationwide is convince Republican members of the House and Senate that climate change is not a conspiracy invented by scientists to waste taxpayer money on thermometers.</p>
<p>(Are Republican members of the House and Senate <em><strong>really</strong></em> that stupid? The answer is a resounding NO, but acknowledging reality has an adverse effect on the size and frequency of campaign contributions&hellip;)</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637636,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;giantkid&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77637636" title="Link to this comment">#9.2</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 12:46 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77639770"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77639770,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;stephenstralka&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Stephen Stralka&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://stephenstralka.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=StephenStralka81645B87-377C-BE87-0088-3C64E624DD14.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://stephenstralka.newsvine.com/">Stephen Stralka</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77639770" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>That's the thing, "pro-growth" solutions to the climate/energy crisis are lying around all over the place. We need to rebuild our whole freaking infrastructure anyway, so there are all kinds of fortunes to be made in all the new markets that would develop if we committed the resources to doing it green.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77639770,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;stephenstralka&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">4 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77639770" title="Link to this comment">#9.3</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 1:51 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77644712"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77644712,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://sandyc954.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=sandyc954508CABD8-29C5-8E38-4000-6320D55A0014.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://sandyc954.newsvine.com/">sandyc954</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77644712" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Our county (not Berkeley/Alameda), but a more agricultural zone nearby has that program. It is something locals should ask their County/Parish Supervisors to put into play.</p>
<p>It encourages the solar usage, keeps people working, both in PG&amp;E/electricity provider and the installers. Best case would be using panels made in CA...or encourage their locals to start a manufacturing plant for the inverters, wiring, panels, frames, nuts and bolts, even.</p>
<p>We have just had a decision in a local <a target="_blank" href="http://www.watchsonomacounty.com/2013/07/cities/santa-rosa-strikes-deal-on-sonoma-clean-power/">town to use Clean Energy</a>.</p>
<p>This can be done if we urge the locals <strong>to act</strong> or act ourselves.</p>
<p>It is clearly a larger problem, but getting more people to find ways of accomplishing clean energy, rather than nixing it is called for.</p>
<p>Some towns have solar panels on the rooftops of their buildings.</p>
<p>I have solar panels on my rooftop. It feels good to do something about it, but if you can't yourselves, advocate for your locals to find ways that would work, not just say no and deny.</p>
<p>Even if it is just for good health of people, this could lead to a larger solution with the added bonus of jobs. There can be jobs that do not come from oil pipelines and fracking operations. Not doing one thing in oil, coal or natural gas, where water is contaminated and wasted does not mean no jobs, it means <em>different</em> jobs.</p></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77644712,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77644712" title="Link to this comment">#9.4</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 3:57 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77659040"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77659040,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;joanmj&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Joan in Sacramento&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://joanmj.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://joanmj.newsvine.com/">Joan in Sacramento</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77659040" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>9.1 Slappy, I don't buy my electricity from a private company, I am a customer of the Sacramento Municipal Utility District, a publically-owned utility. SMUD has an elected Board and is a very forward-looking organization, encouraging energy efficiency and solar power generation (I have solar electric panels on my roof that generate about half of my annual usage). I am stuck with investor-owned PG&amp;E for my natural gas. SMUD has some of the lowest rates for electricity in the State of California.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77659040,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;joanmj&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77659040" title="Link to this comment">#9.5</a> - Wed Jul 17, 2013 1:24 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77637348"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77637348,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;cinderellassister&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Cinderella&#039;s Sister&quot;}"></div><a name="star11"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star12" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://cinderellassister.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=cinderellassister0E4D4E1B-5B3A-2998-8098-D1EF951ED91D.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://cinderellassister.newsvine.com/">Cinderella's Sister</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77637348" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><blockquote>
