ss="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://mdborn.newsvine.com/">Md born</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77641494" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Well I wish he'd illuminate all of us on those brilliant market based ideas those thinkers are sitting on, anonymously of course.  </p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77641494,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;mdborn&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77641494" title="Link to this comment">#15</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 2:36 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77645313"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77645313,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Glen Runciter&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/">Glen Runciter</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77645313" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>The real problem with all this is he felt he needed to do it anonymously. Think about that- this is a concept already embraced by most of science, not some far out theory. And he felt he could not put his name alongside those in the science community, without I guess fear of some sort of reprisal. Wow. Not much room for discourse in that party, I guess.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77645313,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77645313" title="Link to this comment">#16</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 4:14 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77645529"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77645529,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;danzaemon&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Danzaemon&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://danzaemon.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://danzaemon.newsvine.com/">Danzaemon</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77645529" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Does it really matter if a politician here or there -- be this individual conservative, pseudo-conservative, moderate, liberal, etc. -- realizes the dangerous reality of climate change?</p>
<p>These days, a US politician's one and only job is to raise money in order to stay in office. The two most successful tactics for this are: (1) placate wealthy sponsors, or (2) threaten wealthy sponsors.</p>
<p>The wealthiest of any politician's sponsors for the foreseeable future will be those in the energy industry, and ascendant energy sources are currently very bad for the environment. Anyone with fingers in coal, oil, natural gas, and similar energy-related products (automobiles, shipping, etc.) will deny climate change for vital business reasons.</p>
<p>So a politician can either kill any legislation that might alleviate climate change, or he can push such legislation for the purpose of being paid to relinquish it. Any politician who doesn't take advantage of such tactics will lose elections to those who do.</p>
<p>The result is that nothing will change in US politics... while catastrophic changes develop in the environment.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77645529,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;danzaemon&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77645529" title="Link to this comment">#17</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 4:20 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77645969"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77645969,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Glen Runciter&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://glenrunciter.newsvine.com/">Glen Runciter</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77645969" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Its not true that all will deny it. Yes, it may only happen when they are effected by dollars, but that is starting to happen. One report recently had caught my eye...it was produced by PriceWaterhouseCoopers, one of the world's largest tax, audit, and consulting firms, and they advise many Fortune 500 clients all over the world. If interested, here it is and it is quite sobering. This is what they are advising these large clients:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.pwc.com/gx/en/sustainability/publications/low-carbon-economy-index/index.jhtml"><a href="http://www.pwc.com/gx/en/sustainability/publications/low-carbon-economy-index/index.jhtml">http://www.pwc.com/gx/en/sustainability/publications/low-carbon-economy-index/index.jhtml</a></a></p>
<p>Businesses are more and more getting the message. Will it be too late? Maybe. But relegating ourselves to catastrophe is not what future generations would expect of us.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77645969,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;glenrunciter&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77645969" title="Link to this comment">#17.1</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 4:32 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77646485"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77646485,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;callingalltoasters&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;calling all toasters&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://callingalltoasters.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://callingalltoasters.newsvine.com/">calling all toasters</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77646485" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I wonder what won first place in the 'Young Conservative Thought Leaders' contest?  I'm going to guess "Al Gore is a poopyhead and he has a big house, so there libtards!"</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77646485,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;callingalltoasters&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77646485" title="Link to this comment">#18</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 4:45 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77650397"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77650397,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;thebugman2&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;TheBugMan&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://thebugman2.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=thebugman2348F5CD9-7432-CB2B-D898-281FD04909D9.uncropped.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://thebugman2.newsvine.com/">TheBugMan</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77650397" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p><em>"...Someone in the GOP needs to say it: conservation is conservative; climate change is real; and conservatives need to lead on solutions because we have better answers than the other side. [...]"</em></p>
<p>Really?  Are you kidding?  I thought proposing and/or promoting ANY solution the the climate change crisis was strictly <em><strong>verboten</strong></em> in the republican party.  Does anyone on the right even contemplate reducing greenhouse gases or reducing our dependence on fossil fuels?  Could any of them bring up subsidizing green energies, such as wind or solar, like they subsidize Big Oil?  Give me a break.</p>
<p>[If true this probably will open up a Senate seat in Oklahoma as James Inhofe will have a heart attack and keel over, shocked at the heresy now lurking in the republican party]</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77650397,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;thebugman2&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77650397" title="Link to this comment">#19</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 6:25 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77653968"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77653968,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://sandyc954.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=sandyc954508CABD8-29C5-8E38-4000-6320D55A0014.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://sandyc954.newsvine.com/">sandyc954</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77653968" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Just goes to show folks, this current TPub bunch, even before TP sre not conservative, they should stop saying they are.</p>
<p>They are wholly owned corporate shills. Bowing to oil, coal and gas corps. They keep building that empire, which is far from conservative.</p>
<p>Barry Goldwater would scold these people, shaming their use of religion/religious people to gain power.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77653968,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77653968" title="Link to this comment">#19.1</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 8:37 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77661695"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77661695,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;climateconservative&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Climate Conservative&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://climateconservative.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://climateconservative.newsvine.com/">Climate Conservative</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77661695" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>"Conservation is Conservative" is a trademarked slogan for ConservAmerica (aka Republicans for Environmental Protection).</p></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77661695,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;climateconservative&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77661695" title="Link to this comment">#19.2</a> - Wed Jul 17, 2013 8:34 AM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77668323"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77668323,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://sandyc954.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=sandyc954508CABD8-29C5-8E38-4000-6320D55A0014.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://sandyc954.newsvine.com/">sandyc954</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77668323" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I gave that an up, because I hope to see <em>that group</em> strengthened. Conservatives cannot deny the conservation of resources is conservative.</p>
<p>The EPA is about preserving resources, keep the land from being consumed and eroded, the water clean, air breathable without harmful increases of PPM particles or gases. Removing <em>all the trees</em> without replanting as they go has to stop.</p>
<p>My Dad was fairly conservative. He died from lung disease, living in an area where concentrated pollution was a known problem. The steel mill employed people, but there were 2 smoke stacks going constantly, plus the cars we dearly love were increasing with population increasing, the highways grew.</p>
<p>We need to limit pollution and find solutions where we keep cars but use cleaner emissions, use mass transit to keep cars from idling in traffic jams, stop contaminating water, which we need to live, air we need to live.</p>
<p>This is absolutely something government should do.</p>
<p>My problem is Republicans are all about deregulating commerce and promoting corporate profit at all costs. Abolish the EPA calls are heard.</p>
<p>If we are going to say free market, then promote some corporations to trample over us, that is not free market any more. At least hold them to standards that do not pollute the essentials and say let's reverse the damage we've done.</p>
<p>These "conservatives" are not conservative, they are enablers of rampant pollution, dangerous activities, oil spills, earth, water and air contamination.</p>
<p>That is the kind of conservatism I can embrace, <strong>not</strong> what is passed off today with privacy, peoples bodies and their family make-up- being the states' business, state sponsored discrimination/outright control of people is not something I can ever embrace.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77668323,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77668323" title="Link to this comment">#19.3</a> - Wed Jul 17, 2013 12:18 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77671559"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77671559,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://sandyc954.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=sandyc954508CABD8-29C5-8E38-4000-6320D55A0014.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://sandyc954.newsvine.com/">sandyc954</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77671559" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>p.s. They seem a little like Log Cabin Republicans to me.</p>
<p>So, my best hope is for a total spin off from the TPubs than would be a counter to the phony conservatives we have. That party is beyond comprehension for me to have anything to do with them.</p>
<p>Their issues would hopefully not be treated as some fake Green claim in products that are not really Green.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77671559,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;sandyc954&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77671559" title="Link to this comment">#19.4</a> - Wed Jul 17, 2013 1:45 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77651575"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77651575,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;spinnakerasmiguel&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Miguel -&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://spinnakerasmiguel.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://spinnakerasmiguel.newsvine.com/">Miguel -</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77651575" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I don't know what the author is worried about. It's not as if the Teabillies who would disagree with him can read ...</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77651575,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;spinnakerasmiguel&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77651575" title="Link to this comment">#20</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 7:03 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77651770"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77651770,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;pangaea2&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Pangaea&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://pangaea2.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://pangaea2.newsvine.com/">Pangaea</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77651770" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Here is the pattern that is being followed by Americans at large, sans scientifically literate Americans:  deny the climate is changing...admit the climate is changing but humans have nothing to do with it...oh crap, the climate is changing, and we are at fault.  We as a country are at part II, and I hope it is not too late before we get to part III.  </p>
<p>The only good thing that could possibly come from a Republican winning the white house in 2016, and I choke when I say this, is that said Republican could claim Climate Change as their issue and run with it.  Do I hold out hope for this...nope.  But if Hillary, and Elizabeth or any other Democrat wins the white house in 2016, we can expect more of the same.  Yes the black guy would be out, but think about it, did they treat Clinton any better?  </p>
<p>Still, climate Climate Change (upper case intended) is the overriding and most important issue of our day that almost nobody is willing to do anything about.  Even Obama was late on the issue, and it is yet to be seen if he will follow through on his proposed actions.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77651770,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;pangaea2&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77651770" title="Link to this comment">#21</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 7:11 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77653650"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77653650,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jeremyxz&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Jeremy-xz&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://jeremyxz.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://jeremyxz.newsvine.com/">Jeremy-xz</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77653650" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>When Mitt Romney was in the primaries and admitted what every leading science organization in the world has stated; Global Warming is real and caused by human emissions, Rush L. cried that his run for President was over. So the next day he retracted his statement and was lying to get the GOP on his side.</p>
<p>Sad for America</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77653650,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;jeremyxz&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77653650" title="Link to this comment">#22</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 8:23 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c77654706"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77654706,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;pangaea2&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Pangaea&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://pangaea2.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://pangaea2.newsvine.com/">Pangaea</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77654706" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Isn't it interesting that political parties are not mentioned in the constitution?</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77654706,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;pangaea2&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77654706" title="Link to this comment">#22.1</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 9:10 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77657355"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77657355,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;armis32200&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;armis32200&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://armis32200.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://armis32200.newsvine.com/">armis32200</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77657355" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Republicans, like the Taliban, consider apostasy a capital sin.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77657355,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;armis32200&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77657355" title="Link to this comment">#23</a> - Tue Jul 16, 2013 11:19 PM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77660209"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77660209,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;roytoxicboy&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;roytoxicboy&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://roytoxicboy.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://roytoxicboy.newsvine.com/">roytoxicboy</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77660209" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>A "conservative" solution would be pricing pollution and adding it to the cost of any and all products and services. This added cost to energy production would level the playing field across the entire sector. Instead the argument is being framed, in the fossil fuel world, as a "carbon tax". A semantic sleight of hand that diverts the eye from the subsidy, that not paying for the damage a product does, truly is.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77660209,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;roytoxicboy&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77660209" title="Link to this comment">#24</a> - Wed Jul 17, 2013 5:16 AM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c77661603"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77661603,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;climateconservative&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Climate Conservative&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://climateconservative.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://climateconservative.newsvine.com/">Climate Conservative</a></div></div><div id="commentText_77661603" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Bill O'Reilly believes climate change is real. <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZD39QY8ew3c"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZD39QY8ew3c">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZD39QY8ew3c</a></a></p></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:77661603,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;19504184&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;climateconservative&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c77661603" title="Link to this comment">#25</a> - Wed Jul 17, 2013 8:29 AM EDT</span><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-paginate_Paginate"><a name="discussion_nav"></a><span class="jump">Jump to discussion page: </span><span class="curPageLink">1</span> <a href="http://maddowblog.msnbc.com/_news/2013/07/16/19504184-nervous-gop-staffer-climate-change-is-real?pc=25&sp=25#discussion_nav">2</a><div class="clearfix"><span></span></div></div></div><div class="commentcontainer"><div class="vine-p p-comment_CommentForm commentfields use_zinger"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;canLink&quot;:true,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3769109&quot;,&quot;isPrivate&quot;:false}"></div><a name="entercomment"></a><div class="commentbody"><div class="c_author"><div class="user"><a><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" d